{"id":"north-country","term":"North country","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>A general name for the countries that lay north of Palestine. Most of the invading armies entered Palestine from the north (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 41:25\">Isa. 41:25</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 1:14\">Jer. 1:14</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 1:15\">15</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 50:3\">50:3</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 50:9\">9</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 1:15\">41</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 3:1\">51:48</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezekiel 26:7\">Ezek. 26:7</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Isaiah 41:25","Jeremiah 1:14","Genesis 1:15","Genesis 50:3","Genesis 50:9","Exodus 1:15","Exodus 3:1","Ezekiel 26:7"]}